99
01:28:32,550 --> 01:28:43,750
[HOST]: So, A I's primary function in these fields is to drive down the costs of those type sub-layers within the larger token industry? Is that its main contribution?

100
01:28:43,750 --> 01:29:24,550
[MIRA]: Precisely. A I can, and will, drive down the costs of those type sub-layers, often to incredibly low levels, approaching zero marginal cost for certain tasks. But the token sub-layers will remain largely unaffected in terms of their fundamental cost structure. So, the overall effect isn't a widespread, exponential collapse of all costs. Instead, it's a dramatic and often counter-intuitive redistribution of costs, where the expenditure becomes increasingly concentrated on the token layers. The parts that can be cheap become extremely cheap, but the parts that are inherently bespoke remain expensive. The cost ratios shift, but the exemption for token work persists.

101
01:29:24,550 --> 01:29:30,150
[HOST]: You mentioned exemption earlier. Is that the concept from the title of your article?

102
01:29:30,150 --> 01:31:34,400
